<div3 type="orders" n="1" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><hi rend="smallcaps"><placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>,</hi> <dateStruct value="1864-09-20" full="yes" authname="1864-09-20"><month reg="09" full="yes">September</month> <day reg="20" full="yes">20</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="302" /><rs n="Exchange Notice 12">Exchange Notice No. 12</rs>.--All officers and men of the <rs>Vicksburg</rs> capture of <dateStruct value="1863-07-04" full="yes" authname="1863-07-04"><month reg="07" full="yes">July</month> <day reg="4" full="yes">4</day>, <year reg="1863" full="yes">1863</year></dateStruct>, who reported for duty at any people camp cast of the <rs>Mississippi</rs> prior to <dateStruct value="1864-09-19" full="yes" authname="1864-09-19"><month reg="09" full="yes">September</month> <day reg="19" full="yes">19</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>, are hereby declared exchanged. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Ould,,Robert,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00138" reg="default:Ould,Robert,,," authname="ould,robert"><foreName full="yes">Robert</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Ould</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><rs type="role" reg="Agent of Exchange">Agent of Exchange</rs>.</signed> <term type="printrun">se 21--6t</term> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="2" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><hi rend="smallcaps"><orgName n="Treasury Department" type="department">Treasury Department</orgName>,<lb /><placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States of America</placeName>,<lb /><placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>,</hi> <dateStruct value="1864-09-17" full="yes" authname="1864-09-17"><month reg="09" full="yes">September</month> <day reg="17" full="yes">17</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="303" />Regulations for the <name>Assignment</name> of <num value="0.04">Four Per Cent</num> Certificates or Bonds, Issued under the <name>Act</name> of <dateStruct value="1864-02-17" full="yes" authname="1864-02-17"><month reg="02" full="yes">February</month> <day reg="17" full="yes">17</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>, and Held by Officers or Soldiers in the <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States</placeName> army. --These Certificates or Boards may be assigned in presence of the <rs type="role" reg="commanding-Officer">commanding officer</rs> or adjutant of the regiment to which the party holding the some may belong, to be endorsed by such officer in the words, "Executed before me," and signed officially. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Trenholm,,G.,A.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00139" reg="default:Trenholm,G.,A.,," authname="trenholm,g.,a."><foreName full="yes">G.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">A.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Trenholm</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><rs type="role" reg="Secretary">Secretary</rs> of the <unclear>T</unclear></signed> <term type="printrun">se 21--12t</term> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="3" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><hi rend="smallcaps"><placeName reg="Enrolling office">Enrolling office</placeName>,<lb /><placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>,</hi> <dateStruct value="1864-09-12" full="yes" authname="1864-09-12"><month reg="09" full="yes">September</month> <day reg="12" full="yes">12</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="304" />The Following Circular from the <rs type="place">Bureau of Conscription</rs> is published for the information of all concerned: </p> 
<div4 type="entry" n="1" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><hi rend="smallcaps"><placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States of America</placeName>,<lb /><orgName n="War Department" type="department">War Department</orgName>,<lb />Bureau of Conscription,<lb /><placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond, Va.</placeName></hi> <dateStruct value="1864-09-09" full="yes" authname="1864-09-09"><month reg="09" full="yes">September</month> <day reg="9" full="yes">9</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="305" /><rs n="Circular 30">Circular No. 30</rs>. </p> 
<p> Commandants of Conscripts will instruct County Enrolling Officers to proceed diligently, with the aid of the <rs>Temporary Board</rs>, to make a complete registration of every white male resident in their respective counties, between the ages of <unclear /> and <measure n="50years" type="date">fifty years</measure>, not actually serving in the army in the field or with the reserves. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="306" /> The name, age, occupation and physical condition of the persons registered, together with the <unclear /> of exemption, or dated, or other reason for not being in active military service, will be stated in there Registers.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="307" />Special care will be taken in stating <unclear> </unclear> though briefly, the causes which <unclear /> the person from being sent to the army; and not to <unclear /> any person from the registration not serving in the army in the field or with the reserves. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="308" /> These Registers must be Rewarded to the <unclear /> before the <dateStruct value="-10-15" full="yes" authname="--10-15"><day reg="15" full="yes">Fifteenth</day> of <month reg="10" full="yes">October</month></dateStruct> Next, To accomplish the work in due time, Enrolling Officers and Temporary Boards are enjoined to use the utmost vigor and diligence.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="309" />The information to be thus furnished is regarded as of great importing, and the service must be accurately, as well as promptly, performed. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="310" /> Another, and separate, Register will be, at the same time, prepared and forwarded, of all youths, in each county, who will attain the age of <measure n="17years" type="date">seventeen years</measure> during the next <measure n="12months" type="date">twelve months</measure>. In this last-named Register will be stated the month when these youths will attain the age designated. </p> <closer> By command of <signed><rs type="role" reg="Brigadier-General">Brigadier-General</rs> J. <num value="3">3</num>. <persName n="Preston,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00140" reg="mostcommon:Preston,nomatch:0" authname="preston"><surname full="yes">Preston</surname></persName>, Superintendent.</signed> <lb /> <signed>(Signed) <persName n="Duffield,,C.,B.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00141" reg="default:Duffield,C.,B.,," authname="duffield,c.,b."><foreName full="yes">C.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">B.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Duffield</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><rs type="role" reg="Assistant-Adjutant General">Assistant Adjutant-General</rs>.</signed> </closer> </div4> 
<div4 type="entry" n="2" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="311" /> In compliance with the foregoing Circular, all male white residents of the <rs type="place">City of Richmond</rs>, between the ages of <num value="16">sixteen</num> (<num value="16">16</num>) and <num value="50">fifty</num>, (<num value="50">50</num>) years, are hereby notified that they are required to report for the purpose of registration at the following named places in their respective wards: </p> </div4> 
<div4 type="entry" n="3" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><persName n="Ward,,Monroe,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00142" reg="default:Ward,Monroe,,," authname="ward,monroe"><foreName full="yes">Monroe</foreName> <surname full="yes">Ward</surname></persName>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="312" /> <rs n="At 306">At No. 306</rs>, corner of <address><street n="Broad Street">Broad</street></address> and <address><street n="Foushee Street">Foushee</street></address>, on Tuesday and <dateStruct value="-09-20" full="yes" authname="--09-20"><day type="name" full="yes">Wednesday</day>, <month reg="09" full="yes">September</month> <day reg="20" full="yes">20th</day></dateStruct> and <dateStruct value="-09-21" full="yes" authname="--09-21"><day reg="21" full="yes">21st</day></dateStruct>, from <time value="8am">8 A. M.</time> to <time value="6pm">6 P. M.</time> </p> </div4> 
<div4 type="entry" n="4" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><persName n="Ward,,Madison,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00143" reg="default:Ward,Madison,,," authname="ward,madison"><foreName full="yes">Madison</foreName> <surname full="yes">Ward</surname></persName>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="313" /> At <placeName><placeName reg="City Hall">City Hall</placeName></placeName>, <orgName>office of City</orgName> Collector, on Thursday and <dateStruct value="-09-22" full="yes" authname="--09-22"><day type="name" full="yes">Friday</day>, <month reg="09" full="yes">September</month> <day reg="22" full="yes">22d</day></dateStruct> and <dateStruct value="-09-23" full="yes" authname="--09-23"><day reg="23" full="yes">23d</day></dateStruct>, from <time value="8am">8 A. M.</time> to <time value="6pm">6 P. M.</time> </p> </div4> 
<div4 type="entry" n="5" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><persName n="Ward,,Jefferson,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00144" reg="default:Ward,Jefferson,,," authname="ward,jefferson"><foreName full="yes">Jefferson</foreName> <surname full="yes">Ward</surname></persName>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="314" /> At First <placeName reg="Market Hall">Market Hall</placeName>, on Monday and <dateStruct value="-09-26" full="yes" authname="--09-26"><day type="name" full="yes">Tuesday</day>, <month reg="09" full="yes">September</month> <day reg="26" full="yes">26th</day></dateStruct> and <dateStruct value="-09-27" full="yes" authname="--09-27"><day reg="27" full="yes">27th</day></dateStruct>, from <time value="8am">8 A. M.</time> to <time value="6pm">6 P. M.</time> </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="315" /> The registration will be confined to the <rs>Corporate Limits</rs> of the <rs type="place">City of Richmond</rs>, and will be <unclear /> under the superintendence of the <name>Advisory</name> <unclear />--It will include all exempts on any ground <unclear /> detailed soldiers, detailed conscripts, and <unclear /> </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Fiord,,William,H.,Blat," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00145" reg="default:Fiord,William,H.,Blat," authname="fiord,william,h.,blat"><foreName n="William" full="yes">Wm.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">H.</foreName>  <foreName full="yes">Blat</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Fiord</surname></persName>.</signed> <lb /> <signed><rs type="role2">Lieutenant</rs> and <placeName reg="Enrolling Officer City">Enrolling Officer City</placeName> of <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>.</signed> <term type="printrun">as <unclear />--<unclear /></term> </closer> </div4> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="4" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><hi rend="smallcaps"><placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States of America</placeName>,<lb /><orgName n="Subsistence department" type="department">Subsistence Department</orgName>,</hi><lb /><placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>, <dateStruct value="1864-09-16" full="yes" authname="1864-09-16"><month reg="09" full="yes">September</month> <day reg="16" full="yes">16</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="316" />Notice to Holders of Claims against the <orgName n="Subsistence department" type="department">Subsistence Department</orgName>.--On the <dateStruct value="--30" full="yes" authname="---30"><day reg="2" full="yes">30th</day></dateStruct> of the present month the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of the Treasury">Secretary of the Treasury</rs> will withdraw the long-date <num value="0.06">six per cent</num> non- taxable bonds from the market and hold them for a higher rate.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="317" />All persons holding claims against the <rs>Government</rs> for subsistence stores are hereby interned that if they wish there bonds in payment of their claims they must <unclear /> this Bureau or the purchasing officer of the last, <hi rend="italics">in scriting,</hi> before the <dateStruct value="--30" full="yes" authname="---30"><day reg="30" full="yes">30th instant</day></dateStruct>, in order to see cure the bonds at the present low price. </p> <closer> (Signed) <signed><persName n="Northrot,,L.,B.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00146" reg="default:Northrot,L.,B.,," authname="northrot,l.,b."><foreName full="yes">L.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">B.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Northrot</surname></persName>.</signed> <lb /> <signed><rs type="role" reg="Commissary-General">Commissary General</rs> of Subsistence Official.</signed> <lb /> <signed><persName n="Brewer,,L.,B.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00147" reg="default:Brewer,L.,B.,," authname="brewer,l.,b."><foreName full="yes">L.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">B.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Brewer</surname></persName>,</signed> <rs type="role2">Major</rs> and <rs type="role" reg="Commissary of Subsistence">Commissary of Subsistence</rs>. <term type="printrun">se 17--t<unclear /></term> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="5" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><hi rend="smallcaps"><orgName n="Treasury Department" type="department">Treasury Department</orgName>,<lb /><placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States of America</placeName>,</hi><lb /><placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>, Va, <dateStruct value="1864-08-26" full="yes" authname="1864-08-26"><month reg="08" full="yes">August</month> <day reg="26" full="yes">26</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="318" />Regulations for Carrying into Effect the <name>Act</name> of Congress Approved <dateStruct value="1864-06-13" full="yes" authname="1864-06-13"><month reg="06" full="yes">June</month> <day reg="13" full="yes">13</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>, Authorizing Owners of Registered <num value="0.08">Eight Per Cent</num> Bonds, Issued under the <name>Provisions</name> of the <rs>Act Approved</rs> may <num value="16">16</num>, <dateStruct value="1861--" full="yes" authname="1861"><year reg="1861" full="yes">1861</year></dateStruct>, to Exchange the same for <rs n="coupon bond" type="product">Coupon Bonds</rs>--Parties owning registered <num value="0.08">eight per cent</num>, bonds under the act of <dateStruct value="1861-05-16" full="yes" authname="1861-05-16"><month reg="05" full="yes">May</month> <day reg="16" full="yes">16</day>, <year reg="1861" full="yes">1861</year></dateStruct>, desiring to exchange them for <rs n="coupon bond" type="product">coupon bonds</rs>, will assign them, in the manner pointed out in the printed endorsement on the back of the certificate, to the "<placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States of America</placeName>, in exchange for <rs n="coupon bond" type="product">coupon bonds</rs>, " and cause them to be presented to the <name>Register</name> of the <orgName n="Treasury Department" type="department">Treasury Department</orgName>, who will thereupon, in compliance with the provisions of the set of <dateStruct value="1864-06-13" full="yes" authname="1864-06-13"><month reg="06" full="yes">June</month> <day reg="13" full="yes">13</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>, issue <rs n="coupon bond" type="product">coupon bonds</rs> for the amount specified in the <rs n="registered bond" type="product">registered bonds</rs> so assigned. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Trenholm,,G.,A.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00148" reg="default:Trenholm,G.,A.,," authname="trenholm,g.,a."><foreName full="yes">G.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">A.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Trenholm</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><rs type="role" reg="Secretary of the Treasury">Secretary of the Treasury</rs>.</signed> <term type="printrun">au 29--ts</term> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="6" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head rend="smallcaps"><orgName n="Treasury Department" type="department">Treasury Department</orgName>,<lb /><placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States of America</placeName>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="319" />Loans on the <name>Security</name> of the <num value="5000000.06">five hundred Million Six Per Cent.</num> Non-taxable Bonds, under the <orgName type="regiment" key="7Section">Seventh Section</orgName> of the <rs>Currency Law</rs>.--Deposits on call will be received by the <rs>Treasurer</rs> in this city, <rs type="role" reg="Assistant-Treasurer">Assistant Treasurers</rs> at <placeName reg="Charleston, Kanawha, West Virginia" key="tgn,7013583" authname="tgn,7013583">Charleston</placeName> and <placeName reg="Mobile, Mobile, Alabama" key="tgn,7017444" authname="tgn,7017444">Mobile</placeName>, and the <name>Depositaries</name> at <placeName reg="Wilmington, New Hanover, North Carolina" key="tgn,7014631" authname="tgn,7014631">Wilmington</placeName>, <placeName reg="Raleigh, Wake, North Carolina" key="tgn,7013949" authname="tgn,7013949">Raleigh</placeName>, <placeName reg="Columbia, Maury, Tennessee" key="tgn,2098585" authname="tgn,2098585">Columbia</placeName>, <placeName reg="Augusta, Richmond, Georgia" key="tgn,7017498" authname="tgn,7017498">Augusta</placeName>, <placeName reg="Savannah, Chatham, Georgia" key="tgn,7014487" authname="tgn,7014487">Savannah</placeName> and <persName n="Montgomery,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00149" reg="mostcommon:Montgomery,nomatch:0" authname="montgomery"><surname full="yes">Montgomery</surname></persName>, and certificates will be <unclear /> for the same, bearing interest at the rate of <num value="0.04">four per cent</num> per annum, and secured by the hypothecation of an amount of the above bonds equal to the some of these loans.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="320" />The bonds to be set apart by the <rs>Treasurer</rs>, and the proceeds, when sold, applied exclusively to the payment of the said certificates. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="321" /> The security and convenience afforded to banks and other corporations, and to the public genitally, by this mode of temporary investment, and the affect of the measure, if generally adopted, in keeping the currency within moderate bounds, it is hoped will commend it to the favorable consideration of the community and secure their prompt co-operation in carrying it into effect. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Trenholm,,G.,A.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00150" reg="default:Trenholm,G.,A.,," authname="trenholm,g.,a."><foreName full="yes">G.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">A.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Trenholm</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><rs type="role" reg="Secretary of the Treasury">Secretary of the Treasury</rs></signed> <lb /> <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName> <dateStruct value="1864-07-22" full="yes" authname="1864-07-22"><month reg="07" full="yes">July</month> <day reg="22" full="yes">22</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>. <term type="printrun">au 22--ts</term> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="7" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><hi rend="smallcaps"><orgName n="Treasury Department" type="department">Treasury Department</orgName>,<lb /><placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States of America</placeName>,</hi><lb /><placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>, <dateStruct value="1864-08-08" full="yes" authname="1864-08-08"><month reg="08" full="yes">August</month> <day reg="8" full="yes">8</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="322" />Certificates of Indebtedness Bearing <num value="0.06">Six Per Cent</num> Per Annum Interest and Free from Taxation — By the <orgName type="regiment" key="14Section">fourteenth section</orgName> of the act to reduce the currency, approved <dateStruct value="1864-02-17" full="yes" authname="1864-02-17"><month reg="02" full="yes">February</month> <day reg="17" full="yes">17</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>, the <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of the Treasury">Secretary of the Treasury</rs> is authorized to issue the above certificates, payable <measure n="2years" type="date">two years</measure> after the ratification of a treaty of peace with the <placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">United States</placeName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="323" />They cannot be sold, but are only to be issued to such creators of the <rs>Government</rs> as are willing to receive the same in payment of their demands.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="324" />They must also be given at par, though free from taxation. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="325" /> The attention of purchasing agents and disbursing officers of the <rs>Government</rs> is called to this class of public securities as offering peculiar advantages to those from whom the supplies of the <rs>Government</rs> are bought; and to facilitate the use of them, checks drawn by disbursing officers upon the depositaries holding these funds, and marked across the face "payable in certificates of indebtedness," will be paid in conformity therewith. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="326" /> Depositaries are hereby authorized and required to comply with this regulation, and to make application to the <name>Register</name> for supplies of certificates as required. </p> <closer> (Signed) <signed><persName n="Trenholm,,G.,A.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00151" reg="default:Trenholm,G.,A.,," authname="trenholm,g.,a."><foreName full="yes">G.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">A.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Trenholm</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><rs type="role" reg="Secretary of the Treasury">Secretary of Treasury</rs>.</signed> <term type="printrun">au 22--ts</term> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="8" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><hi rend="smallcaps"><orgName n="Treasury Department" type="department">Treasury Department</orgName>,<lb /><placeName reg="United States" key="tgn,7012149" authname="tgn,7012149">Confederate States of America</placeName>,</hi><lb /><placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>, <dateStruct value="1864-07-28" full="yes" authname="1864-07-28"><month reg="07" full="yes">July</month> <day reg="28" full="yes">28</day>, <year reg="1864" full="yes">1864</year></dateStruct>.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="327" />Taxed Treasury Notes.--In order to promote, as far as practicable, the early liquidation by the <name>Treasury</name> of the <rs>Outstanding Taxed Notes</rs>, the <rs>Treasurer</rs>, <rs type="role" reg="Assistant-Treasurer">Assistant Treasurer</rs>, and Pay Depositaries in the different States, are hereby authorized to receive the said notes, except the <measure n="100dollars" type="currency">$100</measure> notes, at <num value="66">66</num><unclear /> per centum, on deposit, <unclear>isuing</unclear> for same certificates of loan, upon hypothecation of non-taxable bonds.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="328" />The said certificates to be payable on demand after the expiration of <measure n="90days" type="date">ninety days</measure>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="329" /> And all agents for the sale of the above bonds are hereby authorized to receive the taxed notes, with the exception above named, in payment of bonds, when sold, at the rate of <num value="66">66</num> <unclear /> per centum. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Trenholm,,G.,A.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00152" reg="default:Trenholm,G.,A.,," authname="trenholm,g.,a."><foreName full="yes">G.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">A.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Trenholm</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <signed><rs type="role" reg="Secretary of the Treasury">Secretary of the Treasury</rs>.</signed> <term type="printrun">au 22--ts</term> </closer> </div3> </div2> 
